        {
          "username": "RG",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "100481765901136462587",
          "user_review_count": 4,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLH5Mr3ok4zXBAYWvWSBuA_pZEs1ZQH5yBrVHVUE8MoWDuHxw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I didn\u2019t have high expectations for my visit as a new patient as I\u2019ve found most visits to Dr\u2019s offices in NYC to be impersonal, disinterested and rushed. I was so happy to have the opposite experience at MOM. I was met and taken back to one of the exam rooms by Emily who is lovely. She took her time and was kind and thorough (she\u2019s going to make a great doctor one day!). She was present throughout my visit aiding Dr. Seilhan and coordinating and setting up a device I need to wear for the next few days. MOM is lucky to have her during her year off before med school!\n\nDr. Seilhan was awesome. She was patient, thorough, asked questions and listened. She was genuinely interested in my care and nothing was rushed. I haven\u2019t had a primary care physician for a few years but that changed today.\n\nShout out to Skye at the front desk who patiently helped me setup my labfinder account!\n\nI would recommend them to anyone!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tkT2JGRm1jelp5V25CMGFWUTNiMDR3VTFGRlZsRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x25e4f724faca6735!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkdObFFmczZyWnB0aVQ3b04wU1FFVlE%7C%7C?hl=en",
